My colleagues at the University of Oxford and I started a research project in Uganda to study the economic life of refugees.
We chose Uganda not because it is typical of the receiving countries.
It is precisely an exception.
Unlike most of the host countries in the world, what Uganda has done is afford economic opportunities for refugees.
Give them the right to work, give them freedom of movement.
The results are staggering, both for refugees and host countries.
