Economist Evan Ross created the concept of pairing markets, that is, the order of preferences of both sides determines the final match.
My colleagues Will Jones and Erik Stett Boe, who are studying how to apply this concept to solve the refugee problem, they asked refugees to rank their preferred countries, but at the same time allowed countries to sort the types of refugees they wanted to receive, based on skill or language criteria, and finally matched the two sortes.
