Most of the tragedies and chaos that we see in Europe are completely avoidable.
This is a fundamental contradiction in the European asylum policy: In order to seek refuge in Europe, you have to get to Europe on your own after a dangerous journey that I described earlier, but why these journeys are necessary.
In an era of low-cost airlines and consulates?
These are completely unnecessary journeys last year, which led to the deaths of more than three thousand people on European borders and within Europe.
If refugees can go directly to Europe and seek asylum, we can avoid these deaths, and we can do so through humanitarian visas that allow people to collect visas at embassies or consulates in neighboring countries and then pay for them to arrive in Europe by cruise ship or plane.
